Right. You have the right to (i) know what personal data we collect, use, disclose, "share" and sell, (ii) delete your personal data, (iii) correct your personal data, (iv) limit the use of your personal data and disclose your sensitive data (v) receive a copy of your personal data, and (vi) third You have the right to opt-out of "sharing" your personal data with third parties for personalized advertising purposes on the party's site. Such requests can be made on your own or through a delegated agent. When using an approved agent, we provide detailed guidance to the agent on how to exercise their privacy rights (https://privacy.microsoft.com/ccpa-guidance). For more information on how to exercise these rights, please see our Notice of Data Privacy Laws in U.S. states (https://aka.ms/USStatePrivacyNotice).
	
Universal opt-out. Microsoft receives and responds to the Global Privacy Control (GPC) browser opt-out signal. If you receive GPC signals from a user who visits our site, Microsoft will disable the sharing of user data with third parties related to personalized advertising.
	
You may have additional rights related to your Consumer Health Data, as defined by your applicable state's Consumer Health Privacy Act. For the rights available under Washington State's My Health My Data Act (MHMDA) and other applicable U.S. consumer health privacy laws, please see the Consumer Health Data Privacy Policy (https://privacy.microsoft.com/microsoft-consumer-health-data-privacy-policy).
	
If you have a Microsoft account, you can exercise your rights through the Microsoft Privacy Dashboard (https://account.microsoft.com/privacy). This requires a login to your Microsoft account. If you have any additional requests or questions after using the dashboard, contact Microsoft at the address in the How to contact (https://privacy.microsoft.com/privacystatement#mainhowtocontactusmodule) us section or use the web form (https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=2126612)or call us toll-free in the United States at +1 (844) 931 2038. If you do not have an account, you can still contact us in the manner described above to exercise your rights. To further protect your personal data, we may verify your identity by asking for additional information such as your country of residence, email address, and phone number before accepting your inquiry.
	
To indicate your choice to opt out of sharing your personal data with third parties in order to display personalized ads on third-party sites, please visit our Sharing Opt-Out page (https://aka.ms/yourcaliforniaprivacychoices). You can also visit the opt-out page (http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=286759) to control the personalized ads you see on your Microsoft properties.
	
We will not use or disclose your Sensitive Data for any purpose other than as described below and as permitted or required by applicable law. That's why we don't offer features to limit the use of sensitive data.
	
If you have made a request to Microsoft to know, delete, correct, or receive personal information, and you believe that your request has been denied by Microsoft, you can exercise your right to object to the outcome of your request by contacting our Privacy Support team through Microsoft's web form. If your complaint fails and you live in some states, you may have the right to raise your concerns or file a complaint with your state attorney.
	
If you exercise your privacy rights, you have the right not to be discriminated against. Microsoft does not discriminate against users who exercise their privacy rights.
	
